subSubSection.paragraph:
Pronotum (
Fig. 10
) distinctly transverse, lateral margin weakly widened, broadest just basally, surface distinctly deeply punctate, punctation double except for base, punctures consisting of well and deeply impressed punctures, separated approximately by distance equal to their diameter, intermixed with very fine, pinned punctures. Anterior transverse protrusion distinct, sharply semicircular, lateral apophyses present.
